* Regent: Heavy wounds (Тяжёлые ранения) uncommon power of cost 1. Adds a Sharp buff with 3(4) stacks, multiple buffs stacking additively, semantics is "Sovereign blade makes enemy receive 30% (40%) more damage for 2 turns". Internally this buff adds to Sovereign Blade "applies Heavy wounds debuff" (see how Parry does it). Heavy wounds debuff does not stack (similarly to Flanking, several applications stack multiplicatively), lasts 2 turns; example: if originally player played Heavy wounds without upgrade twice, each hit with the Blade will make enemy accept 60% more damage for 2 turns.
* Necrobinder: Call for death, uncommon skill, cost 1. 
  Introduces new keyword "Cast for N", meaning that card creates an Ethereal token of cost 1 that says "Creates a certain card after being played N times.", playing this token card decreases N and returns the token card into hand in the next turn (see Bolas card how it does it). When a card with N = 1 is created, it instead just says "Creates a certain card", and playing it adds that certain card which is free and Exhausts.
  Cast explosion specially says "Apply (39) 52 doom, kill if target's doom is not less than HP. Cast for 3", which means that the eventually created card would be a 0 cost attack that deals 30 damage and exhausts, and intermediate token card should have a reference to this card (check like debuff from Dying star refers to this card, maybe this helps). Doom mechanics is similar to the End of days card.
* Now a similar card for Necrobinder: Song of sorrow, uncommon skill, cost 0. Summons 16(20), heals Osty for 8(10); Cast for 3 turns.
* And another one: Prevents one HP loss, Cast for 2 turns. (Effectively applies Buffer power at the end)
* Necrobinder: Death intention, rare 1 cost, exhausts - select a power card, compose another card (on how to do it, see Mad science card) that adds a copy of previously selected card into Hand of all other players and this intermediate card costs +1 of the original. Those created copies are the same as selected card, but free and etherial.
* Necrobinder: Necrofication, sets ally's HP at 1(10), adds a buff that makes it invulnerable, lasts 5 turns. Innate, retains. 1 cost, requires 2 max energy to sustain effect.
  Sustain ("Поддерживание" in russian) is a new keyword, decreases max energy by certain number until effect wears off naturally or target creature dies.
  Health bar of the target turns entirely cyan, overriding any other colored segments. See how Buffer is implemented. Power of invulnerability should decrement at the start of next turn, not at the end of the current turn, similarly to Intangible buff.
* Necrobinder: uncommon 0 cost. when you play an ethereal card, apply 20 doom to random enemy. When an ethereal card exhausts, get stunned 
* Silent: Hunt down, rare 0 cost - if an enemy has 10 (7) weakness, kill it (twice)

* Nyan cat: colorless 1 cost. Behaves differently for each character:
  * Defect: same as Rainbow
  * Necrobinder: same as Eternal Friendship, but without -1 strength
  * Ironclad: same as Feel no pain
  * Silent: same as Quasar
  * Regent: same as Well laid plans
  * Otherwise: apply 3 regen